configuration/preprocessors.md
     1→# Configuring Preprocessors
     3→Preprocessors are extensions that can modify the raw Markdown source before it gets sent to the renderer.
     4→
     5→The following preprocessors are built-in and included by default:
     6→
     7→- `links`: Expands the `{{ #playground }}`, `{{ #include }}`, and `{{ #rustdoc_include }}` handlebars
     8→  helpers in a chapter to include the contents of a file.
     9→  See [Including files] for more.
    10→- `index`: Convert all chapter files named `README.md` into `index.md`. That is
    11→  to say, all `README.md` would be rendered to an index file `index.html` in the
    12→  rendered book.
    13→
    14→The built-in preprocessors can be disabled with the [`build.use-default-preprocessors`] config option.
    15→
    16→The community has developed several preprocessors.
      →…
